<center><font size="6" color ="red">WHAT IS WXWINDOWS</font></center><br><br>
<font size="5" >* An open source C++ GUI framework to make cross-platform programming child's play. Well, almost.<br><br>
* wxWindows is a 'framework' in the sense that it provides a lot of built-in functionality, which the application can use or replace as required, thus saving a great deal of coding effort. <br><br>

* Link with the appropriate library for your platform (Windows/Unix/Mac, others coming shortly) and compiler (almost any popular C++ compiler), and your application will adopt the look and feel appropriate to that platform.<br><br>

</font>


